<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing a new bumper on your Jeep can significantly enhance its off-road capability and aesthetics. In this article, we'll walk you through the installation of the Excessive Industries NBO Front Bumper on a 2015 Jeep Wrangler Unlimited (JKU). This bumper is designed to fit seamlessly with the rear bumper, providing a cohesive and robust look.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This tutorial will cover everything you need to know about uninstalling your old bumper and installing the new NBO bumper, including the necessary tools, steps, and helpful tips to make the process smoother. The 'Nearly Bolt On' aspect means minimal modification, making it an attractive option for Jeep enthusiasts.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Removing the Old Bumper:</strong> Begin by safely lifting the Jeep. Disconnect any wiring associated with your current bumper, like winch leads and fog lights. Once everything is untangled, remove the bolts securing the old bumper.</li><li><strong>Preparing for Installation:</strong> The NBO bumper requires some cutting to facilitate a proper fit. Use the provided template to mark where to cut on your jeep’s frame. This ensures a snug and secure installation.</li><li><strong>Cutting the Frame:</strong> Using a grinder or cutting tool, carefully cut along your marked lines to remove the necessary material. Be cautious here; safety should be your priority.</li><li><strong>Installing the Winch (if applicable):</strong> Before you install the bumper, it's wise to mount your winch to the new bumper section if you're using one. This can save you troubleshooting later down the line.</li><li><strong>Mounting the Bumper:</strong> With the frame prepared and fairlead attached, position the new bumper on your jeep. Align the mounting holes and use the provided grade 8 hardware to secure the bumper.</li><li><strong>Installing Lighting Options:</strong> If you chose the lower light enclosure, now’s the time to attach your light bar or pods. Make sure they are secured properly to prevent them from bouncing around while off-roading.</li><li><strong>Final Adjustments:</strong> After securing everything, take a moment to check that all connections are tight. This includes the winch and any lights. Double-check that nothing is obstructing the view and that the bumper aligns perfectly.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Keep a vacuum handy to clean up metal shavings from the cutting process. A tidy workspace is essential!</li><li>Test fit all parts before finalizing the installation to avoid multiple adjustments.</li><li>Use anti-seize on all bolts to prevent rust and make future removal easier.</li><li>Consider relocating any components, like the vacuum pump, to allow for better access during installation.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>The installation of the Excessive Industries NBO Front Bumper on your Jeep Wrangler is a straightforward project that can greatly enhance your vehicle's ruggedness and off-road performance. By following these steps and utilizing the provided hardware and template, you can achieve a professional-quality installation in your own garage. Remember, preparation and patience are key; take your time to ensure every component is fitted correctly, and your Jeep will be trail-ready in no time!</p>

